      "span_text": "Concentration of bedrock P is elevated at KS (Table 3) ; thus, if catchment hydrology were similar, one would expect elevated concentrations at KS. Catchment size, and hence meltwater residence time, therefore appears to be an important factor in dictating SRP concentration where bedrock geology is relatively uniform [CITATION_1] .",
